  "divergences": [
    {
      "file": "kernel/schema/tables.mjs",
      "change": "SOURCE_CLASSES gains one member, \"ai-audit\", appended after \"testimony\": [\"primary-measurement\", \"peer-reviewed\", \"preprint\", \"dataset\", \"institutional-report\", \"testimony\", \"ai-audit\"].",
      "rationale": "Adversarial AI research reports (Gemini DR, DeepSeek, ChatGPT arbitration audits of the DG framework) are a grounding source distinct in epistemic status from human testimony; labeling them testimony is honest but faintly insulting to both classes. A one-line, hash-tracked fork, per docs/physics-kernel-recon-report.md Section 2 (\"the source-class question\") and Section 3 seam 3."
    },
    {
      "file": "kernel/compute/transforms.mjs",
      "change": "PACKS gains one member, \"computation\": [\"graph\", \"algebra\", \"statistics\", \"computation\"]. The no-standing rule (never emits \"kernel\", must consume \"values\") and the runtime no-grade-field guard, both previously keyed to pack === \"statistics\", are keyed to a NO_STANDING_PACKS = [\"statistics\", \"computation\"] set instead, so a computation entry obeys the statistics-pack constraints verbatim. No other behavior changes; a statistics entry is affected in no way.",
      "rationale": "Physics numeric transforms (heat-kernel traces, exhaust races, OoM deficits) fit the statistics shape mechanically but are not honestly statistics; a one-line, hash-tracked fork, per docs/physics-kernel-recon-report.md Section 3, seam 3 (\"the compute pack taxonomy\")."
    }
